narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you're humanities-minded and have any interest in French literature I say go for it, this class is great.
Yes! If you are interested in French Intellectual history you will enjoy this class

A very solid introduction to major literary movements in 19th century France. The books we read are all masterpieces and the professor talks a lot about underlying background and connections between movements so that we could better understand the different writers and their works. Workload is totally manageable and reading the novels was a breeze. The in-class quizzes sound daunting for a literature class but they were actually fine. Just make sure to take detailed notes in class. The 2 papers were short and not very stressful (25% in total). Overall the class was not too stressful and you will really enjoy it if you want to know more about French literature.
I would recommend it to another student, particularly one with an interest in French literature who wants to continue developing a pre-existing passion.
